  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, I hope your project deadline went smoothly. It's 6 PM — do you relax with tea before the weekend?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, had a quick chai with team — thanks! Weekend plans? Maybe watch new Bollywood film. You?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're welcome — a team chai is perfect. Watching a Bollywood film sounds fun. Any particular one in mind?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Raaz, maybe — heard it's good. Or maybe something old like Dhoom. What you think?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Raaz is a good pick — and Dhoom is always fun. I think both are great choices. Did you watch Raaz with English subtitles or in Hindi?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, usually watch in Hindi, but sometimes try English subtitles if I feel like improving. But with Raaz, the Hindi version is more... authentic, you know? The dialogues are super Hindi-heavy. Have you seen it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said it — Hindi dialogues in Raaz are full of culture, expressions, and that real Indian flair. I get that — some movies just feel right in their original language. Do you pick Hindi for fun or English for learning?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Mostly Hindi for fun — English is more for work. But sometimes I try to watch Hindi films with English subtitles to learn new words. It's like double the learning! What about you — do you watch Indian movies?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're doing great — using subtitles is a smart way to learn. I watch Indian movies when I can — the music and energy are special. Do you have a song you enjoy from Bollywood?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, I like \"Tum Hi Ho\" from \"Aashiqui 2\" — very romantic. Sometimes sing along in Hindi, even though I don't know the context! But the emotions are universal, you know? What about you — any song you like?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I agree — music carries emotions that cross all languages. \"Tum Hi Ho\" is a classic for a reason. I enjoy songs that make me feel something, like old \"Mere Naam Shabnam\" or \"Pyar Hua Ikrar Hua\". Do you sing Hindi often?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Not often, but when in mood, hum random Bollywood songs while coding. Sometimes drives my team crazy! 😄 You? Sing a lot?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that — music is a great mood booster. My team would probably laugh too if I hummed while working! What song do you hum most often?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Probably \"Chaiyya Chaiyya\" from Dil Se — it's catchy and everyone knows it. But sometimes I do \"Kabira\" from PK — more chill. Okay, I should get back to work. Talk to you soon! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're welcome — \"Chaiyya Chaiyya\" is a great pick! It's fun to hum. I'll be here when you're ready to chat again. Talk soon!"
    }
  ],
